concurrency ---  on:
                    push:
                       branches: [ main ] 
                 concurrency:
                      group: deploy-main
                      cancel-in-progress: true
cancel-in-progess ::: by deafult the cancel-in-progress is false and  the workflows which is running will run and if you execute another workflow it will also run simultaneously.
                       if you mention cancel-in-progress as true : if you triggered a workflow , that is progress and not completed yet and again you triggered another workflow then the 
                       second workflow will be in run automatically (  the previous workflow will be cancelled immediately.)

