Session 12 : 

issues observed on previous workflow 
deploy job failed on windows-latest with nginx image and that caused to workflow failed entirely.To avoid this fail-fast keyword introduced


by default fail-fast  is true 

if we set to fail-fast: false   then if any job fails remaining jobs will still continue to complete the workflow.



max-parallel: 2
fail-fast: false
exclude
include

name: matrix configurations
on: push
jobs:
  deployment:
     name: matrix deployments
     strategy:
       max-parallel: 2
       fail-fast: false
       matrix:
           os: [windows-latest, ubuntu-latest]
           images: [helloworld, alpine]
           exclude: 
              - os : windows-latest
                image: alpine
           include:
              - os : ubuntu-latest
                image: node:alpine
     runs-on: ${{ matrix.os }}
     steps:
       - name: creating a  ${{ matrix.images }} on ${{ matrix.os }}
         run: docker run ${{ matrix.images }}

observations:

total 4 jobs will only run:  windows-latest-helloworld | ubuntu-latest-helloworld | ubuntu-latest-alpine | ubuntu-latest-node:alpine



chat gpt version:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Workflow Basics

Workflow files are stored in .github/workflows/*.yml

A workflow is triggered by events

A workflow contains jobs

Jobs contain steps

Steps run sequentially

Jobs run in parallel by default

2Ô∏è‚É£ Triggers (on)

Common triggers:

push

pull_request

workflow_dispatch (manual trigger)

schedule (cron)

You can filter by:

branches

paths

tags

on:
  push:
    branches: [ main ]

3Ô∏è‚É£ Runners

runs-on: ubuntu-latest (most common)

GitHub-hosted runners:

ubuntu-latest

windows-latest

macos-latest

Self-hosted runners supported

Each job runs on a fresh VM

4Ô∏è‚É£ Jobs

Jobs run in parallel

Use needs to control order

Default max job runtime: 360 minutes

Job-level timeout:

timeout-minutes: 30

5Ô∏è‚É£ Steps

Steps run sequentially

Two types:

run (shell command)

uses (actions)

Step-level timeout overrides job-level timeout

6Ô∏è‚É£ Actions (uses)

Marketplace reusable actions

Syntax:

uses: actions/checkout@v4


Always pin to a version or commit SHA

7Ô∏è‚É£ Environment Variables

Levels:

Workflow

Job

Step

Define using env

Access using:

${{ env.VAR_NAME }} (YAML)

$VAR_NAME (shell)

8Ô∏è‚É£ Secrets

Stored in Repository / Environment / Organization

Access:

${{ secrets.SECRET_NAME }}


Secrets are masked in logs

Secrets are not passed to forks by default

9Ô∏è‚É£ Contexts

Common contexts:

github

env

secrets

inputs

jobs

steps

Example:

${{ github.ref }}

üîü Conditionals (if)

Used at job or step level

if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main'


Default condition: success()

Other functions:

failure()

always()

cancelled()

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ Matrix Strategy

Run jobs with multiple combinations

strategy:
  matrix:
    node: [16, 18]


Default fail-fast: true

Disable:

fail-fast: false

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ Concurrency

Prevent overlapping runs

concurrency:
  group: deploy-prod
  cancel-in-progress: true


cancel-in-progress default: false

